intent_divergence: no intent.md exists for this directory to check against.

`crates/ctx-summarize/tests` provides integration coverage for the summarizer pipeline exercised entirely through hermetic fakes, giving downstream readers confidence that the runner's file I/O, prompt construction, and intent-preservation contracts hold without needing network or real LLM access.

The single file here (`summarize.rs`) owns both the fakes (`FakeFs`, `RecordingAgent`) and the test cases; there's no cross-file coupling to track since this is the only source file in the directory. Its `FakeFs`/`RecordingAgent` pair is the reusable scaffold — any new test in this directory should reuse them rather than re-mocking `Fs`/`Agent`, to keep assertions about prompt content and write ordering consistent.

The load-bearing invariant validated here — leaf-before-rollup write ordering, intent files read-only, and secrets/path-escape rejection — is the pipeline's external contract; any change to the runner that would break these should fail a test in this file first.